How to apply

Exceptional education goes hand-in-hand with genuine care. We combine world-class academics with a deep commitment to truly know and understand each student.

Supporting you from the start

We understand that choosing a school is a significant decision, and our admissions team is here to support your family every step of the way. Let us help you discover how ISSH can be the right fit for your child, and a second home for your family.

Application form

The admissions process

Our admissions process reflects the same care and attention we bring to education; we focus on getting to know you and your child to ensure that ISSH is the school where your child will thrive. From the first enquiry to the first day of school, our admissions team is here to guide you through the process and answer your questions to ensure that both you and your child feel confident about joining the ISSH family.

From Early learning to IB diploma

Our admissions process is personalised and thoughtful. We take time to understand your child’s personality, interests, needs, and aspirations because we believe that a meaningful education begins with strong relationships.

Together, we thrive

We believe each student deserves more than just an education; they deserve a journey tailored to who they are and who they aspire to become. From our nurturing Childcare and Early Learning Programme to the world-renowned IB Diploma Programme and an innovative boarding experience, our school offers pathways for children aged three months to 19 years old. 

Our warm, caring community is what sets us apart. With a personalised approach that values each student’s unique strengths and dreams, ISSH is a place where children flourish academically, socially, and emotionally.

Application requirements:
IB Diploma, Boarding Programme, Secondary School, Primary School, and Early Learning Centre 

The admissions process for the ELC Programme takes approximately two weeks. We have limited places available in both programmes, and we recommend beginning your application early to secure your child’s place. 

We encourage you to schedule a personalised tour of our Childcare and Early Learning where you’ll experience our nurturing and supportive learning environment for yourself.

To learn more, please contact us at [email protected] or call +41 52 624 17 07.

 

After submitting the application documents, we will invite you to visit our school and meet our admissions team in person. We also encourage you to schedule a trial day for your child. For families planning to relocate to Schaffhausen and who are unable to visit us in person, we are happy to meet you online. 

Begin your application

To learn more, please contact us at [email protected] or call +41 52 624 17 07.

When applying for our Secondary School or High School Diploma programmes, please submit your completed application form along with supporting documents, including school reports and letters of recommendation.

We'll arrange academic assessments in English and mathematics, followed by an interview with our admissions team. For local Schaffhausen applicants, we'll also organise a trial period at ISSH to ensure a wonderful fit between your child and our school community.

Begin your application

To learn more, please contact us at [email protected] or call +41 52 624 17 07

Students applying for the IBDP will need to complete the application form and submit supporting documents. We'll conduct an academic assessment to evaluate your child's English and mathematics skills, helping us determine whether the IB programme aligns with their academic strengths and goals.

Following the assessment, we'll arrange a meeting with our academic team to discuss your child's university aspirations and ensure the programme meets their needs. We also encourage scheduling a trial day to give your child a genuine taste of IB learning at ISSH.

We warmly welcome students who are non-native English speakers; however, a certain level of fluency is required to succeed in the programme. Where needed, we may recommend additional language support to ensure your child thrives from day one.

Begin your application

To learn more, please contact us at [email protected] or call +41 52 624 17 07.

ISSH welcomes boarding students from the age of 14 years onwards. To begin your boarding application, we invite you to schedule an online meeting with our admissions team, after which we'll guide you through submitting your application and supporting documents.

We'll arrange assessments in English and mathematics, as well as interviews with both our academic team and our Head of Boarding, who will help you understand the unique benefits of our neighbourhood-style boarding experience.

At any point during the application process, you're welcome to schedule a visit to our school, where you can meet our team, tour our boarding houses, and experience daily life at ISSH.

Make a boarding enquiry

Application form

To learn more about the process, contact us at [email protected] or by phone +41 52 624 17 07.

Empowering Unique Learners

Families choose ISSH because they’re looking for more than just academic excellence – they are looking for a school that truly recognises and celebrates  the uniqueness of each child. Families choose us because we are dedicated to nurturing each student’s growth in a supportive and inspiring environment where each and every child can thrive.

Whether your child is just starting out in our Childcare and Early Learning Centre or working towards the IB Diploma, we provide a caring community that fosters growth, discovery, and an international outlook.

As an IB World School with MSA accreditation, ISSH has consistently achieved strong academic results year after year. For over a decade we have maintained a 100% passing rate for the IB diploma, and our students consistently achieve scores above the global average. These achievements reflect our commitment to excellence and our personalised approach to education.

Our admissions team is here to help

At the International School of Schaffhausen, we understand the importance of selecting the right educational environment for your child. Our team is here to help you! Above all, we aim to ensure a good fit; we want to be sure that ISSH is the right environment for your child, where they will grow, thrive and unlock their potential.
